        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1827_10_27_page01.jpg"/>
                <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
                <opener>
                    <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                        <name type="place" ref="./Placeography.xml#24-Sussex-Place_ENK"/>24 Sussex place Regents park London
                        <date when="1827-10-27"/><hi rend="underline">Oct 27 1827</hi></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <persName>
                            <!-- Use if letter has a saluation ("Dear Sir," for example). If not, delete this line.-->
                        </persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My dear Miss Edgeworth; a young bookseller of my<lb/>
                    acquaintance comes to ask an introduction to<lb/>
                    your notice &amp;, if possible, help in an annual<lb/>
                    work which he is bringing out - an annual<lb/>
                    present, to wit, for children &amp; entitled the Xmas box.<lb/>
                    He has secured the assistance of various people of real<lb/>
                    eminence &amp; I have written to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1">Sir W. Scott</persName> &amp; <del></del> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SoutR1">Mr<lb/>
                        Southey</persName> to the same effect as I am now writing<lb/>
                    to you, &amp; I hope to both with prospect of favourable<lb/>
                    answer. He will of course pay very handsomely<lb/>
                    for any little tale or tale which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                    might honour him -<lb/></p>
                    
                <p>We were all rejoiced with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrewD1"><hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Brewster's</persName> accounts<lb/>
                    of the family of Edgeworthstown town : you will I am sure<lb/>
                    be happy to hear in return that the good folks at<lb/>
                    Abbotsford are very well &amp; that my little boy<lb/>
                    has made a wonderful recovery - Believe me<lb/>
                    always very sincerely your faithful Servt<lb/></p>
                <closer>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">J G Lockhart</persName><!--include linebreaks, if used. example: <closer> Yours<lb/> Very sincerely<lb/> -->
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p><!--A postscript goes here, outside the <closer>. --></p>
                </postscript>
                <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
                <!-- Format for postscripts. 
               Postscripts do NOT go inside closer tags. Adjust to take into account the order in your letter. 
               Sometimes the signature is on page three, the address on page four, then the postscript follows back on the top of page one, for example.-->
